article.description: Monique Coker had 26 points and 11 rebounds to lead Old Dominion to a 75-68 upset of No. 7 Penn State.
article.headline: Coker nails double-double for Lady Monarchs
article.linkText: Old Dominion holds off rally to upset No. 7 Penn St
article.story:
NORFOLK, Virginia (Ticker) -- Monique Coker had 26 points and 
11 rebounds to lead Old Dominion to a 75-68 upset of No. 7 Penn
State.

Coker finished 10-of-13 from the field, grabbed four offensive
rebounds and blocked a pair of shots.

Max Nhassengo had 15 points and five assists and Shareese Grant
added 14 points for the Lady Monarchs (2-2), who held off a late
charge by the Lady Lions by converting 14-of-16 free-throw
attempts in the second half.

Reicina Russell paced Penn State with 17 points and 13 rebounds.
Jess Strom added 17 points and seven assists for the Lady Lions
(1-1), who hit five 3-point field goals and scored 41 points
after halftime, but fell short.

All-American Kelly Mazzante had 14 points on 6-of-16 shooting
and four steals in the loss.
